paragraphs.title: Load Dependency - XML Reader
Load Data Files and Copy to HDFS
paragraphs.text:
%sh

# Download Data from Github
 wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BrooksIan/FAA_SWIM/master/SWIM1.xml -O /tmp/SWIM1.xml
 wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BrooksIan/FAA_SWIM/master/SWIM2.xml -O /tmp/SWIM2.xml
 wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BrooksIan/FAA_SWIM/master/SWIM3.xml -O /tmp/SWIM3.xml

# Make HDFS Directory and Load CSV files into HDFS
hadoop fs -mkdir /tmp/
hadoop fs -put /tmp/SWIM1.xml /tmp/SWIM1.xml
hadoop fs -put /tmp/SWIM2.xml /tmp/SWIM2.xml
hadoop fs -put /tmp/SWIM3.xml /tmp/SWIM3.xml

hadoop fs -ls /tmp/SWIM*

paragraphs.title: Spark Version and Spark Session
paragraphs.text:
%spark2

import org.apache.spark.sql.SparkSession
val spark: SparkSession = SparkSession.builder
  .appName("SWIM Data")  // optional and will be autogenerated if not specified
  .master("local[*]")               // avoid hardcoding the deployment environment
  .enableHiveSupport()              // self-explanatory, isn't it?
  .config("spark.sql.warehouse.dir", "target/spark-warehouse")
  .getOrCreate

spark.version
